This extremely trendy and classy timepiece hails from Casio’s ultra-stylish and highly fashionable range of casual analog watches for women. Perfect for the modern day woman who loves to be seen noticed and admired this exquisitely designed watch gives you not just a multi-functional timekeeper but also a tool that helps you express a strong sense of sophistication and elegance.

This battery powered women’s watch from the house of Casio works on the popular time keeping technology that makes use of small bar shaped crystals of quartz or silicon dioxide. These quartz crystals work by generating an electrical charge which causes them to vibrate at a thousand times a second making them extremely stable resonators for extremely accurate timekeeping.

Body and Design

This highly aesthetic watch from Casio comes with a gently rounded dial measuring 8.4 mm in thickness and contains a light coloured watch face. Apart from the regular time tracking this multi-functional watch is also capable of keeping track of other highly important values and measurements. These secondary measurements are displayed or indicated through the watch’s three sub-dials found within the main dial.

The watch’s multi-functional dial is surrounded by a thick stainless steel case which along with a stainless bezel  forms the upper part of the case and provides the dial with a considerable amount of durability and impact resistance. This bezel that runs around the outer perimeter of the dial is given a brilliant metallic finish which perfectly matches the colour and finish of the stainless steel case.

The three watch hands found housed within the dial sport a bright metallic finish which also extends into the dial’s hour markers. All the hour markers are small metallic rectangular bars except for the 12-hour marker which is featured as a bold metallic numeral. This clever usage of metallic colours over a light solid background gives you great dial clarity for effortless time reading.

This multi-functional dial is comfortably attached to your wrist as long as you desire with the help of the watch’s trendy leather strap. This leather strap can be effortlessly fastened or unfastened with its highly effective push button clasp. With a prominent stainless steel composition and an array of functionalities this specialized women’s watch from Casio manages to weigh just 36.4 g.

Functions and Other Features

The three sub-dials contained within the main dial are responsible for displaying or indicating the 24-hour time format date and day of the week. The sub-dial at the dial’s 3 o’clock position displays the date while the 9 o’clock position sub-dial is used to indicate the day of the week and the third sub-dial at the dial’s 6-hour mark shows you the time in the 24-hour format. All the necessary changes or adjustments to the time date or day of the week can be done through the watch’s rotating screw crown found on the right side of the dial’s case.

The inclusion of a highly scratch-resistant mineral glass cover along with the dial’s sturdy stainless steel case gives the watch a water-resistant capability of up to 50 m. With such sophistication and elegance clubbed with a significant amount of multi-functionality this women’s watch from Casio is sure to find its way into your esteemed watch collection.

This very tastefully designed women’s personal timepiece comes from one of world’s most recognized watch brands Casio and belonging to their popular line-up of casual analog watches for women. This battery powered women's analog watch works on the commonly used quartz crystal mechanism. These quartz crystals work by generating an electrical charge which causes them to vibrate at a thousand times a second making them extremely stable resonators for accurate timekeeping.

Body and Design

This women's personal timepiece from Casio features a contemporary shaped dial that houses a dark coloured watch face. The hour markers on the dial are in the form of metallic bars with the exception of the 12- and 6-hour markers which are bold metallic numerals. All the three time indicating watch hands are also given a similar metallic colour and finish as the hour markers. This clever colour combination used on the dial makes the dial incredibly easy to read the time with nothing more than just a passing glance.

The rectangular dial is surrounded by a sturdy and fashionable case that provides the watch's delicate and minute internal working parts a much needed level of protection and damage resistance. The dial along with its case on this men’s analog watch from Casio is kept safely and comfortably fastened to your wrist at all times by means of the watch’s brilliant bracelet strap that is completely composed of stainless steel and operates an effective push button clasp. 

The dial is given further protection in the form of a hardy glass cover made of mineral crystal material which is known to be significantly scratch resistant. This mineral crystal glass cover of the dial combines well with the dial's protective case to give the watch the highly important feature of being water resistant. The inclusion of ion-plating technology into the case and the bezel gives it a higher level of durability and reduced weight.

All the time related adjustments on this watch can be carried out using the watch’s rotating screw crown that is found on the right side of the dial. With such a high degree of practicality and effectiveness this women's casual watch from Casio speaks volumes about you and your unmistakable sense of style where ever you go.

Body and Design
